##Wuhan, 31 unforgettable days

Wechat, renwumag1980

Feature Introduction, the best Chinese character report

On February 23,2020, the city of Wuhan was closed for a month. Here are 31 clips from Wuhan over the past month, taken from the eyes of front-line journalists and from citizens'social media accounts, that have come together to form one of the city's most memorable memories.

Planning | people editorial

January 23,2020

Light Rain 4 °C ~ 6 °C

January 23,2020

Light Rain 4 °C ~ 6 °C

The city of Wuhan was closed. Taxi driver Li Shaoyun received an order at 3 pm to take a stranded college student back to Ezhou. At the junction of Country Road and national road, she was stopped by a Land Rover. The owner advised her not to go back. Now people can not go out. It was 7:30 p.m. on January 23,2020, and the roads around Wuhan were completely blocked off. Behind the Land Rover, hundreds of cars were lined up, waiting to leave the city. Some of the anxious people got out of their cars and stood by the side of the road, look at the direction of leaving Wuhan.

January 24,2020

Light Rain 4 °C ~ 7 °C

January 24,2020

Light Rain 4 °C ~ 7 °C

New Year's Eve. At 11:44 p.m. , Peng Zhiyong, director of the Department of Critical Care Medicine at Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University, left the hospital. On his way home, he got a phone call from a reporter who asked him if he was stressed. He sighed and seemed to be at a loss for words in the face of some problems. At the end of the interview, after midnight, he said to reporters: "Good New Year, New Year to be safe, before we all say happy New Year, now we say New Year safe. ". Health is all that matters. "

January 25,2020

Sleet 3 °C ~ 4 °C

January 25,2020

Sleet 3 °C ~ 4 °C

On the first day of the Lunar New Year, Qi, a journalist from Wuhan, worked all day by herself. Since January 21, she has been visiting fever clinics and, to avoid the possibility of infecting her family, has moved into her upstairs neighbor's vacant house. This Day's lunch is a bowl of noodles, side dish is the wild vegetable that the mother digs from the wasteland behind the community.

Before the siege, her parents had taken the virus for granted, and had no reserves of vegetables or meat. It wasn't until New Year's Eve that the supermarket's fresh produce section was swept away by nearby residents, devoid of any green. Then, my mother put on a mask to find the mountain has not yet blossomed Canola Moss and shepherd's purse, pick a bag, take home into dumplings, with noodles. It was the only green in Angie's house until the vegetables were back on the market.

January 26,2020

Sleet 3 °C ~ 1 °C

January 26,2020

Sleet 3 °C ~ 1 °C

Hankou hospital nurse@3:30, first day of self-imposed isolation. She wrote it on twitter as follows:

"At 13:00 on the first day of the Lunar New Year, we tried to resuscitate a patient who was highly suspected of pneumonia with our bare hands, without any protective measures, only a mask, a mask and gloves. Many sets of CPR were used to push medicine and defibrillate, i can still hear the sound of his last dying breath, but he didn't make it. He died of a heart attack.

When it was over, I changed into a pointless lab coat, put on a clean mask, put on a latex glove that I had long since forgotten how to break, and went with my colleague to remove all the tubes from his body, after I finished, I rushed to the TAP and washed my hands and face. I knew it would be pointless, but I just wanted to use the cold water to wake me up to what had happened. I just want to cry, I want to go home, but I dare not go home, home and family. It's already happened, so we're on our own.

Colleagues joke that we are also the same life and death, first take a photo, wait for 14 days incubation period we did not get sick well, another one, if not, together in the hospital to make a private room.

It's the first day of quarantine, and I want us to be okay, too.

And I will."

January 28,2020

Sunny-1 °C ~ 8 °C

January 28,2020

Sunny-1 °C ~ 8 °C

Peach, a 38-year-old native of Wuhan, returned to the city with her daughter and mother.

Before this, they traveled to other places, but they had to hide in temporary accommodation in the suburbs to eat instant noodles, fearing that they would be reported because they were from Wuhan accidentally. People from Wuhan who were in other places had set up a temporary wechat group, sharing a variety of ways to get back to Wuhan, peaches buys a high speed train ticket through Wuhan -- Florida is one of the emptiest and quietest high speed trains she has ever ridden, with fewer than 10 people in its carriages.

When we arrived in Wuhan, the train stopped and people got up and got off. Through their masks, they couldn't see each other's faces and only raised their eyebrows to call out to each other. After getting out of the car, Peach said to the Group of friends sitting behind him, "finally come back. ". "

January 29,2020

Sunny-1 °C ~ 12 °C

January 29,2020

Sunny-1 °C ~ 12 °C

A song called "Wuhan Yazi" on this day exploded the circle of Friends of Wuhan People.

This is a commonweal song composed by 3 Wuhan Musicians and sung by 17 Wuhan Artists during the city closure. Each of the singers was in a different part of the country, and they recorded it on their cell phones, and it was eventually sent back to Shanghai synth. The song depicts the most ordinary life in Wuhan, bamboo beds in summer, hot and dry noodles, Yellow Crane Tower road, Jianghan Road, No. 2 Soda Factory... But the video records the streets of Wuhan, which are almost empty, the video ends with the words, "I've never seen Wuhan like this / but I believe / The Bright Sunshine will light up the land / The Cherry blossoms will bloom again / The premature people will still eat the hot dry noodles / the streets will be alive again / we'll take off our masks / go where we want / meet the people we want. "

On the same day, Wuhan Writer Fang Fang reposted the song on Weibo, writing: "tears in my eyes. "

". "

January 31,2020

Clear 0 °C ~ 10 °C

January 31,2020

Clear 0 °C ~ 10 °C

On the high-speed train that stops in Wuhan, a reporter told the conductor that he wanted to get off in Wuhan, and the other said he wanted her to wait for a reply. After a while to a conductor, check identity cards, business cards, and to see the interview letter... Not with the interview letter of the reporter beat the drum, worried about not being allowed.

As a result, the conductor said, "If you don't have a certificate, there's no private passage, and you leave the station with ordinary people. ". " Then the conductor stopped for a few seconds and said earnestly, "when you get off the train, be sure to protect yourself. "after getting off the bus, the reporter saw the first sight of Wuhan, there is a layer of mist, quiet, empty. On the way to the hotel, only a few emergency ambulances passed her, but she always remembered the conductor's eyes, "very bright. ".

February 1,2020

Fine 4 °C ~ 13 °C

February 1,2020

Fine 4 °C ~ 13 °C

Day 10 of the siege of Wuhan. After several days of clear skies, the temperature of the whole city gradually rose. Kinoki, who lives in an old neighborhood Near East L. , opened her balcony window and found a black cat sleeping four stories away on top of a shed in the ground floor courtyard, she could feel the softness of its black fur in the sun and the purr of its belly. She shouted at it, "Hey, cat! "He did not move. The orange cat next to him got up suddenly and went back to sleep.

Kinoki said she had not been downstairs since the siege, but at that moment, she almost had the illusion that she had forgotten about the outbreak, as if it were back in the day. Turning back to reality, she recorded the moment on Douban, writing, "I don't know what page of the future calendar lies on when I can go downstairs and play with my cat. ". "

Image Source: Douban

February 2,2020

CLOUDY TO SUNNY 6 °C ~ 11 °C

February 2,2020

CLOUDY TO SUNNY 6 °C ~ 11 °C

Only two days until Vulcan Mountain hospital receives its first patients. Late at night, there were still workers working all night. The next morning, several workers who had stayed up all night were sitting on the first floor of the ward, smoking to relieve their drowsiness. A reporter came to interview them and asked them if they had any overtime pay for the overnight shift. A small contractor replied, no. Next to them were workers fixing water pipes. They wore thin pink masks and their hands were white from being in the water all day. "These individuals are the most praiseworthy part of such a miracle project, " the reporter wrote in his notes from the day he left Vulcan Mountain to return to his residence. "

February 3,2020

Cloudy to Sunny 0 °C ~ 12 °C

February 3,2020

Cloudy to Sunny 0 °C ~ 12 °C

Shortly after 10:00 a.m. , Zhang Xiaochun, deputy director of the Imaging Department of Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University, posted a message on his facebook page. "Don't be superstitious about nucleic acid testing. CT imaging is highly recommended as the main basis for the diagnosis of 2019-nCoV pneumonia. ". This is the first time that front-line doctors have publicly questioned the reliability of nucleic acid testing. At that time, nucleic acid test was the only basis for the diagnosis of NCP. However, due to the high false negative rate, a large number of suspected patients could not be admitted in time. Two days later, the National Health and Human Services Commission issued the fifth edition of the new coronary pneumonia diagnosis and treatment program, which stipulates CT imaging as the clinical diagnostic criteria (limited to Hubei Province) .

More than 10 days later, in an interview with people, Zhang Xiaochun said that her parents were also infected in the outbreak. Around January 20, when she was checking in her mother for her new crown, she saw many patients in the hospital lobby, some lay on the floor with their bellies in their arms, others with their heads in their arms, some coughing, and she saw the CT scans they were holding, one of which she had taken. "The lungs were white, and, alas, my heart was tingling. "

Dr. Zhang Xiaochun working in front of computer picture source network

February 4,2020

Clear 0 °C ~ 14 °C

February 4,2020

Clear 0 °C ~ 14 °C

Start of spring. In the fever clinic of Wuhan's Fifth Hospital, the infusion room, observation room and emergency room are all crowded and have nowhere to stay. The doors and windows of the emergency room were open, and you could see the doctors operating nervously from the doorway. Outside the clinic, an elderly man in flip flops calmly nibbled on sugar cane. A passing reporter asked him, "why don't you wear a mask? "? It's dangerous out there. " He looked back at the reporter and said, "I'm not afraid of getting sick, I'll die. "The reporter said it was the most relaxed person she had ever seen in Wuhan.

February 5,2020

Sunny to light rain, 3 °C to 15 °C

Several of the orders that volunteer drivers received that day came from front-line nurses.

The nurse on the bus this morning, in her 20s, was crying when she got in. She was told to go home because she had lung problems during a hospital CT screening, but she refused to rest because "my colleagues are on the line and I feel guilty about going home. ".

Another doctor, who is seven months pregnant and lives 18 kilometers from the hospital, said her colleagues are on the front line and she would like to join them. At first, the community has a car to pick people up, but later that she is a doctor, no one dared to drive her, she begged people to take her to work.

After seeing the doctor off, Sung Dong left his car on the side of the road and cried for an hour. From that day on, he said, he still drove a sports car every day, picked up people, and heard a lot of sad, bad, painful stories, but he never cried again.

Sung-dong sent the nurse to work

February 6,2020

Light rain turns to overcast 4 °C ー6 °C

On the second day of the opening of Wuhan's first Shelter Hospital, Fu Shan, who was reading Fukuyama in his ward, became one of the most famous patients. Mr. Fu was one of the first patients admitted to the shelter hospital. On admission, he wore a mask and reclined on his bed reading the origin of political order: from pre human times to the French Revolution, by Francis Fukuyama, a prominent Japanese American scholar. The scene was captured by a reporter from the Hubei daily and went viral online. Francis Fukuyama himself tweeted the photo on Feb. 7. "reading is a refuge to take with you, " lamented many. "

Mr. Fu, 39, is a postdoctoral fellow in the United States who teaches at the Florida State University and specializes in high resolution freeze electron microscopy, the Hubei Daily reported later. This New Year, he returned to visit his parents in Wuhan, did not think of his own and his family have been infected with new pneumonia. In the comments section of the report, readers asked Mr. Fu if he was married, and for a long time after that, Utopia, the publisher of the book, received private messages on Weibo asking, "did that kid from Fukuyama get out of the hospital? "? "

Mr. Fu Reading in the shelter hospital

That night, Kxxkiko, a girl from Wuhan, heard her neighbor playing a "Song of Remembrance" on her trumpet. She opened the window, she recalled. The music was mixed with whistles and applause from other neighbors. She recorded the scene on video and tweeted the 32-second video, saying: "May Music Heal everyone's heart. Good night. ". "

Outside the clinic building of Wuhan Central Hospital, people sent flowers. One of the handfuls was made of Cherimoya. Inside the bouquet was a note that read: "May the next world eat all the world. ". Li Wenliang died at 2:58 a.m. on February 7,2020, according to hospital officials.

February 8,2020

Cloudy to Sunny 1 °C to 10 °C

February 8,2020

Cloudy to Sunny 1 °C to 10 °C

Wuhan Native Zhang Qiong finally found a private dialysis center for her mother. Her mother, 79, has uremia and is on dialysis three times a week. But after the outbreak, the mother often to do dialysis hospital was levied as a fixed-point fever hospital, dialysis room was also closed. Without dialysis, a mother with underlying problems can only survive for a week at the most.

For seven days, she and her mother traveled to hospitals in Wuhan in search of dialysis facilities. Even if the mother's repeated nucleic acid tests were negative, there were no symptoms of new coronary pneumonia, or no dialysis. The reason is that Zhang Qiong's mother has chronic pneumonia, and according to hospital regulations, "as long as there is no admission to treatment of pneumonia. ". That day, Zhang Qiong, who paid for her mother's dialysis at a private dialysis center, said her wish was that they would not be rejected by the private dialysis center next time.

February 9,2020

Sunny 1 °C ~ 13 °C

February 9,2020

Sunny 1 °C ~ 13 °C

In Wuchang's shelter, Fu Dan, a newly diagnosed pneumonia patient, watched his fellow patients perform a spontaneous square dance.

She checked into the shelter three nights ago on a rainy night. On her first day, when the shelter was first built, she slept through a cold, damp, air conditioned night, resting on her valium. The next day, she saw someone collecting garbage, thought it was a cleaner, but later found out it was a roommate. From that day on, Fu Dan, who was in a negative mood, also began to take action and do some voluntary service. On the fourth day of living in the shelter, the heating in the shelter and a new quilt came, the toilet had lights, you could take a bath, and there was a shelter from the rain. Fu Dan remembers that on the night of the dance, the patients purposely entered the same live channel with their cell phones at the same time, giving the music a three-dimensional surround effect. In an interview with people, Fu said, "in fact, the movements are not clear and uniform. They are secondary. It's all about the mood. "

February 10,2020

Light Rain 5 °C ~ 10 °C

Wuhan Girl Wei Wei's mother was released from the hospital on this day. This past January, the girl lost her father and grandmother to new coronary pneumonia, and her mother was hospitalized with the disease. On the day of her discharge from the hospital, Wei Wei's mother returned home for her first meal with a special hubei-style soup of spareribs and fish noodles. The family bought more than 1,000 yuan of meat in advance and wanted her to "have meat for every meal. " The mother herself was also very active, although she could not go out, every day, I'd turn on my phone and do video aerobics. Wei Wei said, after the lifting of the city, the most want to do is to travel with her mother, where is good.

Cai Yi, a doctor at Wuhan Central Hospital, checked his room, took off his protective clothing and opened his mobile phone in the clean area. A MESSAGE POPPED UP ON WECHAT: Lin Jun has left.

He has been doing business for more than ten years. He has become an acquaintance with many doctors and nurses because of his quick and honest work. "The secretary of the hospital director has changed, but he is still here. Two days earlier, Cai Yi had received a phone call from the old head of the anesthesiology department, asking him if he had a bed. He said, "Lin Jun in the canteen has been infected. ". Two days later, in the emergency room of the Central Hospital, Lin Jun left.

Cai Yi sent out a long circle of friends, writing, "we are all little people. Under the baptism of this epidemic, we pay in silence and endure death in silence. ". "

When I was cleaning up the remains, I found a stack of hand-copied music in my grandfather's bag. After the old man's body was taken away, the nurse said, "I'm very sad. "

Valentine's Day. Participating in the construction of the Vulcan Mountain Hospital old Liu infected with new crown pneumonia, in this day into the Vulcan Mountain hospital treatment. His family and his video, from across the screen encourage him, "eat hard, sleep hard, don't think about anything, and you'll be fine soon, " "you'll never have to worry again, lie still every day, don't worry about work outside, " All you can think about is how to eat and sleep, and you win.". The most lovely is his wife, in order to keep him optimistic attitude, to joke with him, "where the food is so good, stay a few more days to go home, the home of eggs and milk are not enough. ".

February 15,2020

Heavy snow-3 °C ~ 4 °C

February 15,2020

Heavy snow-3 °C ~ 4 °C

At a community hospital in Jiang'an District, Wuhan, a middle-aged man arrived in the afternoon wearing a yellow raincoat with a long slit in it. He stopped mobike and looked at the sign at the door, hesitant to come in. Hospitals are empty, policies are posted on doorways, and community hospitals no longer take patients with fevers or see doctors for injections. His mother has had a fever since mid-january and was treated as a suspected new crown patient. She was rushed to various hospitals for examination. Seven CT scans were taken and all were normal. It wasn't until a few days ago that the answer was: a fever caused by advanced stage of liver cancer. He said he didn't want much, just to make her fever go down and feel better.

Unable to drive, he pushed his 75 year old mother through the snow for three hours that morning, found a hospital, was told there would be no injections, and returned shaking. He insisted on coming to the community hospital to try his luck and see if he could get a shot. And I still can't.

He said his family lived on the other side of the river and was locked up on this side of the river to see his mother, but there was also a cancer on the other side of the river whose wife had just had an operation and only her daughter was taking care of her. He hadn't crossed the river for more than 20 days, his clothes crumpled and he wore glasses, and there was a long silence.

From this day on, supermarkets in Wuhan will no longer accept individual purchases, only community group purchases. At the door of Hema Xiansheng at crab point, an elderly man with a blue shopping cart was stopped. He told the clerk that he wanted to buy some fish because he hadn't eaten fish for a long time. He said that he ate pumpkin every day, a day cut in half, eat more than twenty days. The clerk asked him, "why don't you apply for something else? "? " He asked, "with which application? "then his hands were stretched out, and he dragged the little cart away helplessly.

As a volunteer, Qi Qi Qia's job is to call people in Wuhan who had previously called a help line to update them on suspected and confirmed cases of new pneumonia. One day, the patient's grandson answered the phone and said, "my grandfather has gone. For an instant, both sides of the phone fell silent. The day before, Cai Liping, head ICU nurse of Guanggu district of Wuhan's Third Hospital, saw her husband Liu Zhiming off at the entrance of Tongji Hospital. Liu Zhiming, 51, is the director of Wuchang Hospital in Wuhan and the First Hospital director to die from new pneumonia. When the black funeral car carrying Liu Zhiming's body drove out of Tongji Hospital, Cai Liping, wearing protective clothing, chased the car all the way, patting the trunk of the car, crying bitterly, and followed the car for a long distance. One day, a video of Cai Liping crying after her car went viral on the Internet. Some netizens could not help shedding tears after watching the video. "Obviously, I didn't open my voice, but I felt her pain so clearly. ". All anyone's been saying for days is, when this is over, we can do whatever we want, whatever we want, whatever we want. Instead, we're stuck at home, and some of us are stuck in 2020 forever. "

Sunny to light rain, 3 °C to 17 °C

The daily number of newly confirmed cases in Wuhan dropped to three digits for the first time after 17 consecutive days of exceeding four digits. A nurse at the Golden Pool Hospital also had a Long-lost Eight-hour Day, but she told a reporter who had been stationed at the hospital for several days that she might need psychological intervention because she drove back to her home after work every day, his mind was often blank, and he ran red lights so many times that he could not count them. She often can not sleep in the middle of the night, can not sleep to get up to watch the news of epidemic situation, more and more can not sleep.

The reporter asked her what she wanted to do after the outbreak was over? Through the protective clothing, she first smiled, then looked up, thought for a few seconds, suddenly cried, she said she hoped their children college entrance examination smoothly.

February 21,2020

Light rain turns clear 3 °C ~ 15 °C

A reporter recorded in her diary what she saw the day before -- a long line at Hankou Hospital, where elderly people waited to receive medication for chronic conditions such as diabetes and high blood pressure. There was an old man with a number in the 800s, who had been here since 12:00 and waited until after 7:00 p.m. He did not dare to sit on the stool, because of his wife's advice, outside all the railings, seats can not touch, for fear of contamination with the virus. Because of the long stand, plus his high blood pressure, when he went in for his temperature, it was 38.5 degrees. He said he didn't want his son to line up. He's old and he's not afraid to die.

February 22,2020

Yin 3 °C ~ 15 °C

February 22,2020

Yin 3 °C ~ 15 °C

After the outbreak, Wang Fang, a nurse at Wuhan University's Zhongnan Hospital, was in charge of receiving supplies in the logistics department. At noon, a truckload of donated goods arrived at the hospital, among them flowers from Yunnan. Wang Fang was late, the flowers were scarce, and the other departments were already collecting them. Only an unfamiliar colleague, with several handfuls of the flower stalls on the ground sorting. Wang Fang stood a few meters away from his colleague and watched for a moment. The man noticed it, took a few from a bouquet, and said to her through his mask, "here you go. "

The last time Wang Fang received flowers was last summer, on her birthday and the day of her husband's major surgery, but he had them brought to the clinic. Taking a few more roses, Wang Fang carried them home, put them in a bottle, and poured water on them. Tell your husband, "these are flowers from the people of Yunnan. "

February 23,2020

Cloudy 8 °C ~ 18 °C

February 23,2020

Cloudy 8 °C ~ 18 °C

Some of the migrants who stayed in the Wuchang Railway Station because of the siege chose not to take the government's offer of free accommodation, but to take quilts and instant noodles and sleep in underground garages. A 60-year-old man gets up early to read a book every day. Then at 11 o'clock he walks to Han Street, which is five kilometers away, to collect bottles and cardboard and sell waste products. These days, he has finished reading the thick "Kangxi Dynasty" and is studying a book called "micro-expression Psychology" , he said that people have 124 micro-expressions, if you can remember 10 of them, then "do not have to beg" .

A day later, on the morning of Feb. 24, several media outlets simultaneously announced that those stranded in Wuhan would be allowed to leave the city. However, a few hours later, the Wuhan New Crown Pneumonia Epidemic Prevention and Control Headquarters announced that the opening of the Han channel notice invalid, and has been related to the personnel involved in a serious criticism.
